## Testing Best Practices

### 1. Naming Convention
```
MethodName_Should_ExpectedBehavior_When_StateUnderTest

Examples:
- RegisterAsync_ShouldCreateUser_WhenEmailNotTaken
- Login_ShouldReturn401_WithInvalidCredentials
- AddImage_Should_RaiseDomainEvent
```

### 2. Arrange-Act-Assert Pattern
```csharp
[Fact]
public async Task ExampleTest()
{
    // Arrange - Set up test data and dependencies
    var service = new MyService(mockDependency.Object);
    var input = new MyDto { Value = "test" };
    
    // Act - Execute the method under test
    var result = await service.DoSomethingAsync(input);
    
    // Assert - Verify the outcome
    result.IsSuccess.ShouldBeTrue();
    result.Value.ShouldBe("expected");
}
```

### 3. Use Shouldly for Fluent Assertions
```csharp
// Shouldly (GOOD)
result.IsSuccess.ShouldBeTrue();
result.Value.ShouldBe("expected");
users.Count.ShouldBe(3);
exception.Message.ShouldContain("not found");

// xUnit Assert (avoid)
Assert.True(result.IsSuccess);
Assert.Equal("expected", result.Value);
```

### 4. Test One Thing Per Test
```csharp
// BAD - Testing multiple things
[Fact]
public async Task RegisterAndLogin()
{
    await RegisterUser();
    var loginResult = await LoginUser();
    loginResult.ShouldNotBeNull();
}

// GOOD - Separate tests
[Fact]
public async Task Register_ShouldCreateUser() { ... }

[Fact]
public async Task Login_ShouldReturnToken_WithValidCredentials() { ... }
```

### 5. Use Test Fixtures for Shared Setup
```csharp
public class DatabaseFixture : IDisposable
{
    public DbContext DbContext { get; }
    
    public DatabaseFixture()
    {
        DbContext = CreateTestDatabase();
    }
    
    public void Dispose()
    {
        DbContext.Dispose();
    }
}

public class MyTests : IClassFixture<DatabaseFixture>
{
    private readonly DatabaseFixture _fixture;
    
    public MyTests(DatabaseFixture fixture)
    {
        _fixture = fixture;
    }
}
```

